veggies_tagine = Recipe.create(name: "Vegetable tagine with couscous", allergy_code: "VE, NF", ingredient_list: ["1 1/2 cup water", "1/2 tsp salt", "1 cup couscous", "1/4 cup raisins", "1/4 tsp ginger - shredded", "1/4 tsp cardamom powder", "1/4 tsp nutmeg powder", "1/4 tsp cinnamon powder", "1/4 tsp turmeric powder", "1/4 tsp coriander seeds - ground", "1/4 tsp fennel seeds - ground", "1/4 tsp allspice powder", "1/4 tsp black pepper", "1/4 tsp white pepper", "1/4 tsp cayenne powder", "1/4 tsp ground clove", "2 Tbsp vegetable oil", "1 garlic clove - minced", "1/4 cup onion - minced", "1/2 cup potato - small diced", "1/2 cup carrot - diced", "1/4 cup bell pepper - small diced", "1/4 cup zucchini - diced", "1/2 cup (no salt added) canned chickpeas - drained", "1/4 cup olives - pitted", "1 tsp lemon - zest", "1/4 tsp salt", "2 cup vegetable broth", "1/2 Tbsp tomato paste", "1/2 Tbsp olive oil", "1/4 tsp salt"], instructions: "Make the couscous: boil the water and the salt. In a medium bowl, mix dry couscous and raisins. Pour water over the couscous mixture. Cover for 10 minutes. Once the liquid has been absorbed, fluff the couscous with a fork, cover it, and keep it warm.
