falafel = Recipe.create(name: "Falafel with roasted peppers, hummus and cucumber-tomato salad", allergy_code: "GF, VE, NF", ingredient_list: ["1 bell pepper", "1 Tbsp olive oil", "1/8 tsp salt", "1 cup tomato - diced", "3/4 cup cucumber - diced", "1/8 cup red onion - small diced", "1/2 Tbsp dried dill", "1/8 cup parsley - minced", "1 Tbsp olive oil", "1 tsp red wine vinegar", "1/4 tsp salt", "3/4 cup (no salt added) canned chickpeas - drained", "2 Tbsp lemon - juiced", "2 Tbsp tahini", "1 garlic clove", "1 Tbsp olive oil", "1/4 tsp cumin powder", "1/4 tsp smoked paprika", "1 Tbsp water", "1/4 tsp salt", "1 cup (no salt added) canned chickpeas - drained", "1/2 cup parsley - minced", "1/8 cup onion - minced", "1 garlic clove - minced", "1/2 Tbsp cumin powder", "1/2 Tbsp coriander powder", "1/4 tsp chili flakes", "1/2 tsp baking soda", "1/2 tsp salt", "2 Tbsp cornstarch", "2 Tbsp vegetable oil"], instructions: "Make the peppers: turn the oven to 450 degrees F. Line an oven pan with parchment paper. Wash the peppers, brush them with oil, and place them on the tray. Bake until roasted, about 20-30 minutes. Remove them from the oven and place them in a sealed container for 10 minutes. Peel, deseed, and sprinkle them with salt. Set aside until ready to use.
