vegan_paella = Recipe.create(name: "Vegan paella", allergy_code: "GF, VE, NF", ingredient_list: ["1 Tbsp sunflower oil", "1/4 cup onion - diced", "1 garlic clove - minced", "1/4 cup zucchini - diced", "1/4 cup bell pepper - diced", "1/2 cup tomato - diced", "1 bay leaf", "1/8 tsp chili flakes", "1/2 tsp smoked paprika", "1 tsp paella spice blend", "1/8 cup parsley - minced", "1 cup short grain rice", "3 1/2 cup vegetable broth", "1/2 cup (no salt added) canned chickpeas - drained", "1/8 cup olives - chopped", "1/4 cup peas", "1/2 tsp salt", "garnish: 2 lemon wedges"], instructions: "In a large non-stick pot, warm up the vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion and the garlic, cook for 1 minute. Add the veggies, the spices, and the parsley, and cook for about 5 minutes. Adjust with salt. Add the rice and the broth. Gently move the vegetables around so that the rice falls at the bottom of the pot. Cook uncovered at low temperature (maintaining a gentle boil) for 10 minutes. Add the chickpeas, the peas, and the olives. Mix well. Cook for 10 more minutes, rotating the pot often to ensure uniform cooking. If the liquids seem to cook off too quickly, add a little extra broth to avoid the rice sticking to the bottom of the pan. 
